    79Рєњ## Recommended: Use `eslint-plugin-neverthrow`
    81РєњAs part of `neverthrow`s [bounty program](https://github.com/supermacro/neverthrow/issues/314), user [mdbetancourt](https://github.com/mdbetancourt) created [`eslint-plugin-neverthrow`](https://github.com/mdbetancourt/eslint-plugin-neverthrow) to ensure that errors are not gone unhandled.
    82Рєњ
      РєњРђд
   100Рєњ## Top-Level API
   102Рєњ`neverthrow` exposes the following:
   103Рєњ
      РєњРђд
   139Рєњ## API Documentation
   141Рєњ### Synchronous API (`Result`) Рђд
   143Рєњ#### `ok`
   145РєњConstructs an `Ok` variant of `Result`
   146Рєњ
   147Рєњ**Signature:**
   148Рєњ
   149Рєњ```typescript
   150Рєњok<T, E>(value: T): Ok<T, E> { ... }
   151Рєњ```
   152Рєњ
   153Рєњ**Example:**
   154Рєњ
   155Рєњ```typescript
   156Рєњimport { ok } from 'neverthrow'
   157Рєњ
   158Рєњconst myResult = ok({ myData: 'test' }) // instance of `Ok`
   159Рєњ
   160РєњmyResult.isOk() // true
   161РєњmyResult.isErr() // false
   162Рєњ```
   163Рєњ
   164Рєњ[Ргє№ИЈ  Back to top](#toc)
   165Рєњ
   166Рєњ---
   167Рєњ
   863Рєњ### Asynchronous API (`ResultAsync`)
   865Рєњ#### `okAsync`
   867РєњConstructs an `Ok` variant of `ResultAsync`
   868Рєњ
   869Рєњ**Signature:**
   870Рєњ
   871Рєњ```typescript
   872РєњokAsync<T, E>(value: T): ResultAsync<T, E>
   873Рєњ```
   874Рєњ
   875Рєњ**Example:**
   876Рєњ
   877Рєњ```typescript
   878Рєњimport { okAsync } from 'neverthrow'
   879Рєњ
   880Рєњconst myResultAsync = okAsync({ myData: 'test' }) // instance of `ResultAsync`
   881Рєњ
   882Рєњconst myResult = await myResultAsync // instance of `Ok`
   883Рєњ
   884РєњmyResult.isOk() // true
   885РєњmyResult.isErr() // false
   886Рєњ```
   887Рєњ
   888Рєњ[Ргє№ИЈ  Back to top](#toc)
   889Рєњ
   890Рєњ---
   891Рєњ
  1519Рєњ### Utilities
  1521Рєњ#### `fromThrowable`
  1523РєњTop level export of `Result.fromThrowable`.
  1524РєњPlease find documentation at [Result.fromThrowable](#resultfromthrowable-static-class-method)
  1525Рєњ
  1526Рєњ[Ргє№ИЈ  Back to top](#toc)
  1527Рєњ
  1633Рєњ### Testing
  1635Рєњ`Result` instances have two unsafe methods, aptly called `_unsafeUnwrap` and `_unsafeUnwrapErr` which **should only be used in a test environment**.
  1636Рєњ
  1637Рєњ`_unsafeUnwrap` takes a `Result<T, E>` and returns a `T` when the result is an `Ok`, otherwise it throws a custom object.
  1638Рєњ
  1639Рєњ`_unsafeUnwrapErr` takes a `Result<T, E>` and returns a `E` when the result is an `Err`, otherwise it throws a custom object.
  1640Рєњ
  1641РєњThat way you can do something like:
  1642Рєњ
  1643Рєњ```typescript
  1644Рєњexpect(myResult._unsafeUnwrap()).toBe(someExpectation)
  1645Рєњ```
  1646Рєњ
  1647РєњHowever, do note that `Result` instances are comparable. So you don't necessarily need to unwrap them in order to assert expectations in your tests. So you could also do something like this:
  1648Рєњ
  1649Рєњ```typescript
  1650Рєњimport { ok } from 'neverthrow'
  1651Рєњ
  1652Рєњ// ...
  1653Рєњ
  1654Рєњexpect(callSomeFunctionThatReturnsAResult("with", "some", "args")).toEqual(ok(someExpectation));
  1655Рєњ```
  1656Рєњ
      РєњРђд
  1673Рєњ## A note on the Package Name
  1675РєњAlthough the package is called `neverthrow`, please don't take this literally. I am simply encouraging the developer to think a bit more about the ergonomics and usage of whatever software they are writing.
  1676Рєњ
      РєњРђд
